label: Weight specific-ingestion Carbon rate at 15 °C
definition: Weight specific-ingestion Carbon rate at 15 °C. The amount of carbon consumed by an organism at non-limiting concentration of food relative to the individual dry weight measured at 15°C. It is expressed as μg C mg DW−1 h−1
comment: Carbon, at non-limiting conditions -> condition: under non-limiting conditions, food, organism, dry; mass flow rate; at 15°C temperature
